                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1134">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.79658/79: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-15T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 15, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1940. Please telegraph whether decision referred to in your 1921, March 9, has
                    yet been made. Norwegian Ambassador informed us that last week King Haakon
                    accompanied by his Prime Minister<note n="32" xml:id="d1134fn32">Johan
                        Nygaardsvold, Norwegian Prime Minister.</note> and Foreign Minister
                    discussed the matter jointly with Mr. Churchill<note n="33" xml:id="d1134fn33"
                        >Winston S. Churchill, British Prime Minister.</note> and Mr. Eden.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
